to see you sad and cry.

405
00:22:38,890 --> 00:22:40,750
You look so confident.

406
00:22:41,300 --> 00:22:42,710
Khun Kawee...

407
00:22:42,940 --> 00:22:45,060
never said he's
agreed with you yet.

408
00:22:46,690 --> 00:22:48,300
I think you should check your...

409
00:22:48,790 --> 00:22:50,220
ears a little.

410
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:52,820
There might be
something wrong with your ears.

411
00:22:52,930 --> 00:22:55,010
I told you, didn't I?

412
00:22:55,720 --> 00:22:58,820
That in a moment,
he'll have a boyfriend.

413
00:23:02,820 --> 00:23:05,470
I think you should move to your table.

414
00:23:06,510 --> 00:23:10,360
Sitting here will only make you sad.

415
00:23:10,380 --> 00:23:12,270
Is P'Phupha trying to win me over?

416
00:23:13,720 --> 00:23:15,790
I'm dead, I'm dead, I'm dead.

417
00:23:15,820 --> 00:23:17,590
My heart is shaking like hell.

418
00:23:18,030 --> 00:23:19,870
Max, Max!

419
00:23:19,900 --> 00:23:20,650
What?

420
00:23:20,670 --> 00:23:23,200
I think we should go back to our
table, the momentum is not right.

421
00:23:23,230 --> 00:23:24,250
Let's go, get up.

422
00:23:24,270 --> 00:23:27,720
N'Thum, sit here with me.

423
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:30,010
Looks like the atmosphere is not good.

424
00:23:30,040 --> 00:23:32,930
Anyway, thank you
for the money kha, Auntie.

425
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:34,600
Hurry up, Max. Let's go.

426
00:23:37,590 --> 00:23:39,750
I'm spending money on a sissy?!

427
00:23:39,780 --> 00:23:41,010
Oh dear!

428
00:23:42,740 --> 00:23:44,170
Cheer up.

429
00:23:44,440 --> 00:23:48,100
As the saying goes,
desire blinds the eyes.

430
00:23:48,100 --> 00:23:51,050
To the point of not
realizing that he's a sissy.

431
00:23:51,210 --> 00:23:52,660
What do you want?

432
00:23:52,970 --> 00:23:55,300
You know that in your heart.

433
00:23:56,690 --> 00:23:58,530
You want to open a
fight table with me, right?

434
00:23:58,580 --> 00:23:59,750
Sure.

435
00:23:59,830 --> 00:24:01,470
Wanna duel like we did the other day?

436
00:24:01,860 --> 00:24:03,600
That's enough!

437
00:24:06,030 --> 00:24:08,440
No need to have any duel today.

438
00:24:08,660 --> 00:24:10,420
Just have chill drinking.

439
00:24:11,220 --> 00:24:13,720
Ai'Mai, let's switch places.

440
00:24:14,890 --> 00:24:16,430
Why do you want to switch places?

441
00:24:21,840 --> 00:24:25,630
If I let you sit next to Ai'Mai,
you'll have a duel again.

442
00:24:25,820 --> 00:24:27,820
Someone might
die if you're not taking easy.

443
00:24:28,380 --> 00:24:30,830
We won't fight,
just let him sit here is good.

444
00:24:30,830 --> 00:24:31,360
Right?

445
00:24:31,360 --> 00:24:32,900
It's good, right?

446
00:24:33,300 --> 00:24:34,430
That's right.

447
00:24:34,570 --> 00:24:36,430
Sit like this is better.

448
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:38,930
Am I right, N'Kawee?

449
00:24:39,980 --> 00:24:41,140
Yes.

450
00:24:41,380 --> 00:24:43,710
Sit like this is better.

451
00:24:44,300 --> 00:24:47,040
So we can see
each others' face clearly.

452
00:24:47,180 --> 00:24:49,110
Am I right, P'Tonmai?

453
00:24:49,850 --> 00:24:51,040
Yes.

454
00:24:51,450 --> 00:24:53,260
How much did I just spent?

455
00:24:54,810 --> 00:24:56,610
So many.

456
00:25:07,070 --> 00:25:09,120
Do you want me to
send you home, N'Kawee?

457
00:25:19,580 --> 00:25:20,990
I mean...

458
00:25:21,340 --> 00:25:24,790
do you want me and
Ai'Mai send you home?

459
00:25:26,180 --> 00:25:28,520
It's alright, you guys go ahead.

460
00:25:33,070 --> 00:25:35,400
I want to have
someone send me home.

461
00:25:35,580 --> 00:25:38,070
I feel so dizzy here.

462
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:40,750
Ai'Phupha, let's go home.

463
00:25:40,850 --> 00:25:41,890
I'm sleepy.

464
00:25:43,470 --> 00:25:45,000
Let's go.

465
00:25:45,030 --> 00:25:46,080
Why are you standing there?

466
00:25:46,330 --> 00:25:49,060
Then, I'll take my leave.

467
00:25:57,360 --> 00:25:59,090
- P'Kawee
- What?

468
00:25:59,120 --> 00:26:00,320
Those two...

469
00:26:00,570 --> 00:26:02,520
